main event: The witness observed two unidentified objects in the sky for around 1.5 hours on May 2, 1960.
interesting points: One object was round and silhouetted against the sky, appearing white in color. It remained in the west, maneuvering for 4.5 hours.
The objects appeared as lights and followed a steady pattern for 4.5 hours.
The witness was a metal worker who viewed the objects from his location.
The report concludes that due to it being a single witness case, the sighting is classified as insufficient data, but it is likely the witness observed a light reflection from a stationary source.
The objects did not make any sound.
sighted object: two unidentified objects, one round and one shaped like a boomerang
